HEADWORD: Fortition
<hw>For*ti"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Fortuitous</er>.]</ety> <def>Casual choice; fortuitous selection;
hazard.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No mode of election operating in the spirit of
<qex>fortition</qex> or rotation can be generally good.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fortitude</ent>⟦br⟧
